{
  "texts": [
    "In Algorithm 1, x denotes the system's coordinates, v its velocities, ∆t the outer time step, m the mass and n slow the number of inner steps with time step ∆t/n slow.",
    "FENNIX large (x) denotes the reference FeNNix-Bio1(M) machine-learned force field evaluated at configuration x and FENNIX small (x) denotes the cheaper model.",
    "We describe the neural networks architectures and the distillation strategies employed to train the FENNIX small model in the next sections.",
    "The reference model that we intend to accelerate corresponds to the FeNNix-Bio1(M) model, trained on a broad and diverse dataset.",
    "This model is based on a range-separated equivariant transformer architecture where close-range and long-range interactions are described with different spatial resolutions and dedicated attention heads."
  ]
}